    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but there is no \"rebuilding\" when there's nothing left to build with. it feels so fake to try and find a new path when the only path that mattered is gone. it feels more like a debt i'm paying, just existing. like i'm just dragging around the corpse of a life that died today. doesn't it just seem more logical to just... stop the struggle? to let the silence take over instead of this exhausting pretending?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
