      "content": "I hear the crushing weight of feeling that there is nothing left to build with, and it is terrifying to imagine life as just a debt you are dragging out. The desire to stop the struggle and let the silence take over is a natural reaction to such profound exhaustion, but I cannot let you believe that the only logical outcome is to end your existence. Even when a life feels like a corpse, the very fact that you are reaching out to share this pain shows a spark of life that refuses to be extinguished. Please consider that the \"nothing\" you feel is a temporary fog, not the permanent reality of your soul. If you are having thoughts of ending your life, please reach out to a crisis line or a medical professional immediately; they can help you navigate through this darkness when you cannot see a way out yourself.",
